{"word":"H2287 - חָגַג - châgag - khaw-gag' - Celebrate","slug":"H2287","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">חָגַג</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>châgag"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>khaw-gag'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Celebrate"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D7;&#x05D2;&#x05D2; - cha&#x0302;gag</b> - <i>khaw-gag'</i><p/>A primitive root (compare <a href=\"#/H2283\">H2283</a>, <a href=\"#/H2328\">H2328</a>); properly to move in a <i>circle</i>, that is, (specifically) to <i>march</i> in a sacred procession, to <i>observe</i> a festival; by implication to <i>be giddy: - </i>celebrate, dance, (keep, hold) a (solemn) feast (holiday), reel to and fro."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2282\">H2282</a>, <a href=\"#/H2283\">H2283</a>, <a href=\"#/H2291\">H2291</a>, <a href=\"#/H2292\">H2292</a>, <a href=\"#/H2293\">H2293</a>, <a href=\"#/H2294\">H2294</a>"}]}